\section{Script, inline, and relaunch modes}{

\code{launch()} dispatches on the first argument:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Script mode} -- \code{launch("fit.R")} sources a file.
\item \strong{Inline mode} -- \code{launch({ ... })} evaluates a braced block as
tracked code, with no script file on disk. Useful for vignettes,
quick experiments, and one-off tracked runs. The step identifier
is derived from the deparsed expression's hash
(\code{"<inline:<short-hash>>"}), so editing the expression produces a
new tracked step rather than silently comparing against a prior
run's history.
\item \strong{Relaunch mode} -- \code{launch(mr_label("baseline"))} looks up the
most recent run tagged with that label and re-executes its code.
For inline pipelines the stored snapshot on the run row is used
directly. For file pipelines the script file is re-sourced from
disk; if the file is gone, the stored snapshot is used and an
informational message is emitted. The label is auto-inherited
onto the new run unless the caller passes an explicit \code{label}.
\code{launch(mr_run(run_id))} re-executes the specific stored run by
id; the source row's \code{variant_label} (if any) is auto-inherited
onto the new run unless the caller passes an explicit \code{label}.
When the source row's \code{status} is \code{"queued"} (see \code{\link[=queue]{queue()}}),
the call updates that row in place rather than writing a new run
--- \emph{unless} the caller also supplies \code{rebind} or \code{external_inputs},
in which case the queued row is treated as a template body: a new
\code{run_id} is written using the caller's bindings, and the queued
row stays queued for someone else to drain. \code{rebind = mr_binds(...)}
fans the template out into one new run per envelope.
Re-executing a run whose source status isn't \code{"success"} or
\code{"queued"} warns by default (configurable via
\code{options(modelrunnR.relaunch_nonsuccess = c("warn","error","silent"))}).
\item \strong{SQL mode} -- \code{launch("features.sql")} (file) or
\code{launch(mr_sql("..."))} (inline) registers a SQL \code{SELECT} as a
tracked step. The body is a bare query (no \code{CREATE}); modelrunnR
wraps it as \verb{CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW <physical> AS <body>} by
default, or \verb{CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE} when \code{materialize = TRUE}.
\verb{-- @inputs: name1, name2} and \verb{-- @output: name} headers declare
which modelrunnR-managed names the SELECT references and what to
call the result. See \code{\link[=mr_sql]{mr_sql()}} for the inline form.
}
